    <h1>UOB Paint&#xAD;ing award&#xD;&#xA;Plan in place to ex&#xAD;pand com&#xAD;pe&#xAD;ti&#xAD;tion to other coun&#xAD;tries</h1>
    <h2>&#x2022;</h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201224/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-24"><time>2020-12-24</time></a>
        - <span>FORUM</span>
        - <span role="byline">Ex&#xAD;ec&#xAD;u&#xAD;tive Di&#xAD;rec&#xAD;tor&#xD;&#xA;Group Strate&#xAD;gic Com&#xAD;mu&#xAD;ni&#xAD;ca&#xAD;tions and Brand, UOB</span>
    </section>

    <p>We thank Mr Jef­frey Say Seck Leong (The arts: Paint­ing award should in­clude all Asean coun­tries, Dec 15) and Mr Aaron Gan Ming Ch­ern (Paint­ing award: UOB has helped lo­cal art com­mu­nity,</p>
    <p>Dec 17) for their feed­back and sup­port to up­hold the qual­ity of the UOB Paint­ing of the Year com­pe­ti­tion.</p>
    <p>The com­pe­ti­tion is part of UOB’s com­mit­ment to nurture artis­tic tal­ent and cel­e­brate</p>
    <p>South-east Asian vis­ual arts.</p>
    <p>Ev­ery year, a panel of highly re­spected art ex­perts and artists from the par­tic­i­pat­ing coun­tries se­lects the win­ners through blind judg­ing, with the re­gional top prize de­ter­mined col­lec­tively by the chief judges from all par­tic­i­pat­ing coun­tries.</p>
    <p>We started the com­pe­ti­tion in Sin­ga­pore in 1982 to of­fer artists the op­por­tu­nity to show­case their works to the wider com­mu­nity.</p>
    <p>The com­pe­ti­tion was then ex­tended to Thailand – now in its 11th year – fol­lowed by Indonesia and Malaysia.</p>
    <p>Viet­nam will be the next coun­try as part of our con­sid­ered and long-term ap­proach to ex­pand­ing the UOB Paint­ing of the Year com­pe­ti­tion to other coun­tries across South-east Asia. Lil­ian Chong</p>
    <p>The com­pe­ti­tion is part of UOB’s com­mit­ment to nurture artis­tic tal­ent and cel­e­brate South-east Asian vis­ual arts.</p>


